.Im MicroEmacs command|cursor
.ds C0 "(\fB\*cl\fR)\ \&
.so me.tni
.TH recenter 2
.XI recenter - "\*(C0Recenter the window (refresh the screen)"
.SH NAME
recenter \- Recenter the window (refresh the screen)
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
\fBrecenter\fR \*(C0
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B recenter
scrolls the current window so that the cursor position is at the center of the
window and  redraws  the whole  screen. If \fIn\fR is given then  scrolls  the
window so that the cursor is \fIn\fR lines from the top if \fIn\fR is positive
or from the bottom if negative.
.PP
.B recenter
is typically used to refresh the screen if it is out of date (i.e. needs to be
redrawn).
